description:
Specify the level of cloud-delivered protection.
Not Configured uses the default Microsoft Defender Antivirus blocking level and provides strong detection without increasing the risk of detecting legitimate files.
High applies a strong level of detection.
High + uses the High level and applies addition protection measures (may impact client performance).
Zero tolerance blocks all unknown executables
While unlikely, setting to High may cause some legitimate files to be detected.
We recommend you set this to the default level (Not configured).
